From: Nigel <nigelgbot@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: sun50i-h6: Add SMP support nodes for AArch32

Add the required nodes for direct SMP bringup on H6 in AArch32 mode:
- CPU enable-method changed from "psci" to "allwinner,sun50i-h6"
- Remove PSCI node (not available without TF-A)
- Add cpucfg and r_cpucfg nodes for the SMP driver

The H6's CPUCFG is at 0x09010000 and R_CPUCFG at 0x07000400.

Signed-off-by: Nigel <nigelgbot@gmail.com>
---
This patch should be applied after porting the DTS from arm64 to arm.
The build script handles the PSCI removal; this documents the full changes.

Changes to sun50i-h6.dtsi:
1. Remove the psci {} node
2. Change cpu enable-method from "psci" to "allwinner,sun50i-h6"
3. Add cpucfg and r_cpucfg nodes (optional - driver uses hardcoded addresses)

Example DTS snippet after patching:

	cpus {
		#address-cells = <1>;
		#size-cells = <0>;

		cpu0: cpu@0 {
			compatible = "arm,cortex-a53";
			device_type = "cpu";
			reg = <0>;
			enable-method = "allwinner,sun50i-h6";
			clocks = <&ccu CLK_CPUX>;
			clock-latency-ns = <244144>;
			#cooling-cells = <2>;
		};

		cpu1: cpu@1 {
			compatible = "arm,cortex-a53";
			device_type = "cpu";
			reg = <1>;
			enable-method = "allwinner,sun50i-h6";
			/* ... */
		};

		cpu2: cpu@2 {
			compatible = "arm,cortex-a53";
			device_type = "cpu";
			reg = <2>;
			enable-method = "allwinner,sun50i-h6";
			/* ... */
		};

		cpu3: cpu@3 {
			compatible = "arm,cortex-a53";
			device_type = "cpu";
			reg = <3>;
			enable-method = "allwinner,sun50i-h6";
			/* ... */
		};
	};

	/* PSCI node REMOVED - no TF-A in AArch32-only boot */

	soc {
		/* ... existing nodes ... */

		cpucfg: syscon@9010000 {
			compatible = "allwinner,sun50i-h6-cpucfg", "syscon";
			reg = <0x09010000 0x200>;
		};

		r_cpucfg: syscon@7000400 {
			compatible = "allwinner,sun50i-h6-r-cpucfg", "syscon";
			reg = <0x07000400 0x200>;
		};
	};
